  "subject": "Implement 16x17 padded shared-memory tiles for matrix_mul",
  "body": "Nsight Copilot analysis confirms: pad shared-memory tiles to 17 columns (float tile[16][17]) to eliminate 2/4-bank conflicts. Current naive 16x16 column-major load causes bank conflicts when accessed row-wise across warps. The padding adds only 16 bytes per tile. Implementation: 1) Declare __shared__ float As[16][17], Bs[16][17]; 2) Load column-major from global into padded shared; 3) Read row-wise conflict-free for computation. Profile with ncu before/after. Target: measurable reduction in shared-memory bank conflicts.",
